info.description:
Based on style 4584.

Removes all ads, but keeps important buttons like "Print all", "New window", "Expand all" and "Forward all"

Update (Feb 19 2008)
- Changed position of the "New window" and "Print all" links
*** I hope that this is the most rational solution. Elsewhere links hinder the basic elements of the interface. Please rank it! ***
.yMuNaf {
position:absolute !important;
 left:0 !important;
 top:23px !important;
}

.jsbnre {
 padding-bottom:28px !important;
}

Update (Feb 16 2008)
- Changed position of the "New window" and "Print all" links  (Thanks to user 2833)
.yMuNaf {
position:absolute !important;
 left:450px !important;
 top:-30px !important;
}

Update (Jan 25 2008)
- Added
[class*="gV2Gwc"]{
width : 99% !important;}
Makes the text area for typing the reply of the same length as the original message. (Thanks to user 5792)

Update (Sep 26 2008)
- Added
.iFOJMb {
 display:none !important;
}
Thanks to user  2833

style.css:
@namespace url(http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml);
@-moz-document domain(mail.google.com) {

table[class*="PwUwPb XoqCub MMcQxe"]{
 width : 99% !important;
}

.yMuNaf {
 position:absolute !important;
 left:0 !important;
 top:23px !important;
}

.jsbnre {
 padding-bottom:28px !important;
}

.OZly4d, .m2U49e {
 float:left !important;
 margin-right:10px !important;
}

.yxEQwb, .iFOJMb {
 display:none !important;
}

td.eWTfhb > div.XoqCub {
 width:0px !important;
 overflow:visible !important;
}

td.eWTfhb > div.ice3Ad, div.f3hr3b > table.PwUwPb > tr > td.eWTfhb > div.XoqCub {
 width:100% !important;
}

[class*="gV2Gwc"]{
 width : 99% !important;
}
}
